> what ls -h does
                                                                                                                                                
  The command [36;40;1mls -h[0m is used in Unix-like operating systems (like Darwin) to list the files in a directory, displaying their sizes in a          
  human-readable format. The [36;40;1m-h[0m option stands for "human-readable" and modifies the output of the [36;40;1mls[0m command to display file sizes using unit   
  suffixes (e.g., K for kilobytes, M for megabytes, G for gigabytes) instead of just raw byte counts.                                           
                                                                                                                                                
  Here's an overview of how it works:                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                
  [33;1m • [36;40mls[39;49m:[0m This command lists the files and directories.                                                                                          
  [33;1m • [36;40m-h[39;49m:[0m This option makes the file sizes easier to read.                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                
  For example, instead of displaying [36;40;1m2048000[0m bytes for a file, it would show [36;40;1m2.0M[0m, making it easier to understand the size at a glance.

> explain ls -a permission of files
                                                                                                                                                
  The command [36;40;1mls -a[0m in Unix-based systems (like macOS) is used to list all files and directories in the current directory, including hidden     
  files (those files that start with a dot [36;40;1m.[0m).                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                
  When you mention "permissions of files", it generally refers to the access rights associated with files and directories on the filesystem.    
  Here's a breakdown:                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                
                                                             [1mWhat Permissions Mean:[0m                                                             
                                                                                                                                                
  Permissions define who can read, write, or execute a file or directory. They are typically represented in a triplet format:                   
                                                                                                                                                
  [33;1m 1 [39mOwner (User):[0m The permissions for the file's owner.                                                                                        
  [33;1m 2 [39mGroup:[0m The permissions for users in the file's group.                                                                                      
  [33;1m 3 [39mOthers:[0m The permissions for everyone else.                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                
                                                               [1mPermission Types:[0m                                                                
                                                                                                                                                
  [33;1m • [39mRead ([36;40mr[39;49m)[0m: Permission to read the file or list files in a directory.                                                                        
  [33;1m • [39mWrite ([36;40mw[39;49m)[0m: Permission to modify the file or add/delete files in a directory.                                                               
  [33;1m • [39mExecute ([36;40mx[39;49m)[0m: Permission to execute the file or access the directory.                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                
                                                              [1mViewing Permissions:[0m                                                              
                                                                                                                                                
  When you run [36;40;1mls -a[0m, if you want to see permissions as well, you typically pair it with the [36;40;1m-l[0m option (i.e., [36;40;1mls -la[0m). This provides detailed   
  information. The output will look like:                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                
  [48;5;235m                                                                                                                                            [0m  
  [48;5;235m [38;5;231mdrwxr-xr-x  2 user group 4096 Jul  1 12:00 dir[39m                                                                                             [0m  
  [48;5;235m [38;5;231m-rw-r--r--  1 user group  123 Jul  1 12:00 file.txt[39m                                                                                        [0m  
  [48;5;235m                                                                                                                                            [0m  
                                                                                                                                                
                                                              [1;2mBreakdown of Output:[0m                                                              
                                                                                                                                                
  [33;1m • [0mThe first character indicates the type ([36;40;1md[0m for directory, [36;40;1m-[0m for file).                                                                      
  [33;1m • [0mThe next nine characters are the permissions:                                                                                              
  [33;1m    • [0mThe first three ([36;40;1mrwx[0m) are for the owner.                                                                                                
  [33;1m    • [0mThe second three ([36;40;1mr-x[0m) are for the group.                                                                                               
  [33;1m    • [0mThe last three ([36;40;1mr--[0m) are for others.                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                
                                                                    [1mSummary:[0m                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                
  [33;1m • [36;40mls -a[0m lists all files and directories, including hidden ones.                                                                              
  [33;1m • [0mFile permissions dictate who can read, write, or execute a file.                                                                           
  [33;1m • [0mViewing permissions along with [36;40;1mls -l[0m provides comprehensive file information.
